1
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:12,000
<i>What! They got into
an accident?</i>

2
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:13,700
<i>Jasmine, why did you
leave the house</i>

3
00:00:13,833 --> 00:00:14,900
<i> without telling anyone?</i>

4
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:15,900
<i> Auntie Marj,</i>

5
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:17,733
<i> it was my idea to sneak out.</i>

6
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:19,367
<i> I thought you were nice.</i>

7
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,100
<i>Do you want to put my daughter
in danger?</i>

8
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,500
<i> What were you even thinking?</i>

9
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:26,533
<i>I've been pushing you so that
your grandfather will see you</i>

10
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:29,633
<i> as a worthy successor
to the family's business empire.</i>

11
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:31,100
<i> What about what I want?</i>

12
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:32,900
<i> You only care about yourself.</i>

13
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,600
<i>- You rude little brat!
- Thea, stop!</i>

14
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:36,600
<i> Why are you butting in?</i>

15
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:39,400
<i>Ashley's just your niece, right?</i>

16
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:41,533
<i> Thank you again</i>

17
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,600
<i> for taking the blame for me.</i>

18
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:46,733
<i>Oh my god, Jasmine! Your..
Your nose is bleeding!</i>

19
00:00:46,867 --> 00:00:48,467
<i> Jas, are you okay?</i>

20
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,733
<i>I feel... like everything's
spinning...</i>

21
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:52,300
<i>- Jasmine!
- Jasmine!</i>

22
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:53,867
<i> Oh my god! Jasmine!</i>

23
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,067
<i> Jasmine!</i>

24
00:01:17,067 --> 00:01:19,367
Doctor, what happened?

25
00:01:20,300 --> 00:01:22,600
Her accident was already
a week ago.

26
00:01:22,733 --> 00:01:24,367
We checked everything

27
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:27,500
CT scan, head trauma, whiplash.

28
00:01:27,633 --> 00:01:28,867
Everything came back clear.

29
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,867
Then why did she suddenly
collapse?

30
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:32,500
You're right.

31
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,467
After the accident,

32
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,367
we did all the necessary checks
for internal injuries,

33
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,533
concussion, fractures,
and organ damage.

34
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:44,267
And Jasmine's results
were all normal.

35
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:48,600
So what happened last night
wasn't caused by the accident.

36
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:53,033
By the way, Sir, Ma'am,

37
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:55,833
this is Dr. Alvarez,
our hematologist.

38
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,600
A hematologist?

39
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:01,933
Doctor, why is there
a hematologist here?

40
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:06,300
Ma'am, Sir, we immediately took
a blood sample from Jasmine.

41
00:02:06,733 --> 00:02:09,267
Some of her values are low.

42
00:02:10,267 --> 00:02:12,400
Her hemoglobin is low,

43
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:14,267
her platelets are also low,

44
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:16,300
and there's a high number
of immature

45
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:18,400
white blood cells
in her circulation.

46
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,700
What does that mean, Doctor?

47
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:26,500
Ma'am, these findings could
point to several conditions.

48
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:31,167
But one possibility that we need
to rule out immediately

49
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:34,867
is AML or acute myeloid
leukemia.

50
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:41,233
Leukemia? Cancer?

51
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:46,833
Are you saying my daughter might
have cancer?

52
00:03:42,733 --> 00:03:44,933
Doctor, maybe there's been
some kind of mistake.

53
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:48,833
We know our daughter
has weak lungs.

54
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:51,533
She's always been sickly because
she was born premature.

55
00:03:51,667 --> 00:03:52,733
But...

56
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:56,533
leukemia? Out of nowhere?

57
00:03:57,467 --> 00:03:58,700
Please calm down, Ma'am.

58
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:01,200
It's just our initial
assessment.

59
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:04,933
We still need
to conduct more tests

60
00:04:05,067 --> 00:04:06,833
to confirm her actual condition.

61
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:12,200
So, we will be needing her to
stay here for a little while.

62
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:19,800
We'll start preparing
the tests now.

63
00:04:20,367 --> 00:04:22,300
Excuse me for now.

64
00:04:30,133 --> 00:04:31,767
This is my fault.

65
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:33,967
No, no...

66
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:36,300
I should've watched her
more closely, love.

67
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:39,633
Maybe I would've noticed
the symptoms sooner.

68
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:43,533
All those times
she said she was tired

69
00:04:43,667 --> 00:04:45,567
that she felt dizzy.

70
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:47,633
I should've suspected something.

71
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,200
I should've had her checked
earlier.

72
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,633
Maybe I could've stopped this.

73
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:53,867
This is my fault.

74
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:56,867
Listen to me.

75
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:59,567
Marj, this is not over.

76
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,700
You weren't negligent.

77
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:04,167
You did everything you could

78
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:07,300
to make sure our daughter grew
up strong and healthy.

79
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:10,433
But we can't control everything.

80
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:13,267
Especially her illness.

81
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:17,133
Love, what are we supposed
to do?

82
00:05:19,367 --> 00:05:22,900
Jasmine needs to see
that we're always here for her.

83
00:05:24,233 --> 00:05:27,833
She can't see us scared

84
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:29,733
or worried for her.

85
00:05:31,167 --> 00:05:32,600
Marj, we need to be strong.

86
00:05:34,933 --> 00:05:37,033
So our daughter
can be strong, too.

87
00:06:10,467 --> 00:06:12,367
Ms. Yolly's been standing there
forever.

88
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,900
At this rate, she's going
to scrape a hole

89
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:14,933
through the counter.

90
00:06:20,067 --> 00:06:22,000
Ah, Ms. Yolly...

91
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:26,700
Ms. Yolly, please don't worry
too much about Jasmine.

92
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,400
She always gets through it

93
00:06:28,533 --> 00:06:30,367
whenever she gets sick, right?

94
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:34,333
I don't know, Weng.

95
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:37,500
I just have a bad feeling.

96
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,767
This time, it feels different.

97
00:06:50,367 --> 00:06:51,400
Ma'am.

98
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,033
Miss, ah...

99
00:06:54,833 --> 00:07:00,433
please pack some things
for Marj and Jasmine.

100
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:05,800
Ah, they'll be staying
at the hospital for a while.

101
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:08,300
I'll take care of it, Ma'am.

102
00:07:08,867 --> 00:07:10,233
Come on, help me.

103
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:12,933
We've got it.

104
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,167
Ah...

105
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,833
Ma'am, Jasmine tea.

106
00:07:26,967 --> 00:07:28,500
It might help calm you down.

107
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,833
Jasmine.

108
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:42,000
Try to stay strong, Ma'am.

109
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:45,867
How can I, Miss Yolly?

110
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:54,400
But I can't stop thinking about
what might happen to Jasmine.

111
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:59,300
Paolo said...

112
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:02,800
they think
she might have cancer.

113
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:03,900
What?

114
00:08:07,067 --> 00:08:09,467
My poor granddaughter.

115
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:12,300
She's still so young.

116
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:15,267
She deserves to be exploring
the world

117
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:19,567
and not being stuck in that
cold hospital room

118
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:25,033
with all those needles and
medicines being pumped into her.

119
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:03,867
Ashley?

120
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,100
Where are you going?

121
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:11,500
I'm just going to visit Jasmine
at the hospital, Mom.

122
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,933
I'll go with Oscar.

123
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:16,467
They're bringing some things for
Auntie Marj and Jasmine.

124
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:18,967
No!

125
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,267
You're staying here.

126
00:09:20,833 --> 00:09:23,200
Your grandmother's already sad
about what happened.

127
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:25,000
So just stay and keep her
company.

128
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:29,900
But Mom, Jasmine's sick.

129
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:32,733
She needs me
more than Grandma does.

130
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:34,633
I said no!

131
00:09:34,767 --> 00:09:38,033
What if you catch some germs
there and get sick, too?

132
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,433
Go to your room,
change your clothes.

133
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:42,867
Mom, I'll only be there
for a little while.

134
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,900
I just want to help Jasmine
stay strong.

135
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,200
I'm really worried about her.

136
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:50,767
Why are you being so stubborn?

137
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,333
Wait.

138
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:54,500
Didn't I already tell you
after the accident

139
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:56,867
to stay away from your cousin?

140
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:02,167
I don't want you to be friends
with her anymore.

141
00:10:03,433 --> 00:10:05,100
So just listen to me!

142
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:08,900
Take advantage of the fact that
Jasmine's stuck in the hospital

143
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:10,667
and not in the mansion.

144
00:10:11,233 --> 00:10:14,000
Maybe now you can finally get
closer to your grandparents.

145
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:18,067
And stop giving me that
attitude.

146
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:24,867
Go change!

147
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:38,900
<i> Don't worry, Jas.</i>

148
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:40,633
<i> We're right here.</i>

149
00:10:40,767 --> 00:10:43,000
<i>Everything's going
to be okay, Jasmine.</i>

150
00:10:43,133 --> 00:10:44,933
<i> I don't think I can do this.</i>

151
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:46,567
<i>Maybe we shouldn't go
through with it.</i>

152
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:48,667
<i> Jas, you need this.</i>

153
00:10:50,033 --> 00:10:52,433
<i>We have to find out what's
really going on</i>

154
00:10:52,567 --> 00:10:54,600
<i> so we can make you better.</i>

155
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:58,100
<i> Mom, Dad, I'm really scared.</i>

156
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:00,667
<i> Sweetheart, it'll be quick.</i>

157
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,000
<i> I promise.</i>

158
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:05,100
<i>Don't be afraid.
Your dad and I are right here.</i>

159
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:06,333
<i> We're not going anywhere.</i>

160
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:10,400
<i> We'll just be outside, okay?</i>

161
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:41,533
Hi, Jasmine.

162
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:44,867
Don't worry, we'll do everything
we can to keep you comfortable.

163
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,100
But before we start,

164
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:50,267
we'll need to sedate you
so you won't feel too much pain.

165
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,200
Is it going to hurt?

166
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:53,233
Not really.

167
00:12:33,767 --> 00:12:34,767
Okay, you'll feel a little poke.

168
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,500
We're just going
to take a specimen.

169
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:21,133
Sir, if you need anything
or want me to do something,

170
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,500
just let me know.

171
00:13:24,233 --> 00:13:25,100
Sir?

172
00:13:37,867 --> 00:13:41,400
I'm used to dealing with
problems at the company

173
00:13:41,533 --> 00:13:42,767
on my own.

174
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:50,100
I can handle anything
that comes up at work.

175
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,000
But this...

176
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:56,133
I have no control over it.

177
00:13:57,667 --> 00:14:01,200
I don't even know
how to handle this.

178
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:19,067
Hello, Dad.

179
00:14:22,767 --> 00:14:23,933
What?

180
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:25,600
There's an emergency
at the office.

181
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:28,200
Dad wants me there.

182
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:29,033
What?

183
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:31,267
You're leaving?

184
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,367
Love, I have to.

185
00:14:33,867 --> 00:14:35,533
But I need you here.

186
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:38,900
Can't someone
else deal with it?

187
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:42,300
An investor is trying to
pull out of the company.

188
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:43,667
If I don't show up,

189
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,333
I'll lose the board's
confidence.

190
00:14:46,467 --> 00:14:48,767
They'll think I'm
ignoring the problem.

191
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:51,800
Paolo, your daughter is sick.

192
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,700
Surely they'll understand that.

193
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:57,900
If I don't go,
everything will fall apart.

194
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:00,433
Then we won't have money
for Jasmine's treatment.

195
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:01,467
Is that what you want?

196
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:04,833
For her condition to get
worse or for her to die

197
00:15:07,167 --> 00:15:09,133
just because you don't want me
to leave?

198
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:22,067
Paolo!

199
00:15:27,167 --> 00:15:28,967
Yes, I'm looking forward to it.

200
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:30,633
Bro, thanks.

201
00:15:30,767 --> 00:15:31,467
Thanks for the help.

202
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:33,533
Yeah, okay. Sure.

203
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:34,433
Thanks.

204
00:15:36,067 --> 00:15:37,633
Good news?

205
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:38,667
Yes, actually.

206
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:42,700
My high school friend,
the one I told you about,

207
00:15:42,833 --> 00:15:45,500
the pediatric hematologist,
Ben...

208
00:15:45,633 --> 00:15:47,633
He's willing to work
with Jasmine's doctors.

209
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:52,533
I thought you finally got hired
at one of the jobs

210
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:53,667
you applied for.

211
00:15:55,167 --> 00:15:57,467
So that's why you still
can't find a job.

212
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:00,100
You've been busy with
something else, Edward.

213
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,567
What's wrong with
worrying about Jasmine?

214
00:16:06,067 --> 00:16:07,467
She's my niece.

215
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,933
I want to help her get better.

216
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:14,767
It's fine that you're
worried about her.

217
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:19,833
But maybe you should think
about our family first.

218
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:22,833
Are you really okay
living like this?

219
00:16:22,967 --> 00:16:24,700
Being a burden in this house?

220
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,800
You're the one who wanted us
to live here, remember?

221
00:16:26,933 --> 00:16:29,033
Because I wanted you to
prove to your parents

222
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:30,733
that you deserve a place here!

223
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:34,033
Because I want them to
be proud of you, too!

224
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:36,467
But how is that supposed
to happen

225
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,267
when you're still unemployed?

226
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,367
They're just going to think

227
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,333
you've never done anything
right!

228
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:45,267
That's exactly why
I wanted to help Jasmine!

229
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:51,067
So I could at least
feel like I'm useful.

230
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:54,200
Like we're not just
freeloaders in this house.

231
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:57,500
That's your problem.

232
00:16:58,133 --> 00:17:00,133
The way you make me feel,
you and Dad...

233
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:03,633
You make me feel
like I'm worthless!

234
00:17:03,767 --> 00:17:05,200
Because that's the truth!

235
00:17:06,467 --> 00:17:09,733
Do you think I enjoy
reminding you of that?

236
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:13,800
Do you think I want
a useless husband?

237
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:18,000
If you want me
to be proud of you,

238
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,733
then find a good job.

239
00:17:22,033 --> 00:17:25,233
At least try to catch up
with your brother!

240
00:17:26,867 --> 00:17:28,267
Aren't you embarrassed?

241
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:33,533
Paolo is the CEO of the company,

242
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:35,867
while you keep getting rejected
everywhere you apply.

243
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:36,700
That's enough!

244
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,200
Go ahead!

245
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:47,267
Go! Do it!

246
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:51,367
Prove even more how useless you
are as a husband.

247
00:17:58,800 --> 00:17:59,633
I'm sorry.

248
00:18:02,633 --> 00:18:03,800
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to.

249
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:07,000
Edward...

250
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:12,167
I'm the only one who
hasn't given up on you.

251
00:18:16,167 --> 00:18:18,200
So why are you doing this to me?

252
00:18:20,367 --> 00:18:21,400
I know.

253
00:18:21,567 --> 00:18:22,233
I know.

254
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:23,200
Hon...

255
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:26,533
I'm sorry.

256
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:27,700
I'm sorry, okay?

257
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,367
You're always sorry!

258
00:18:35,067 --> 00:18:36,600
You keep saying sorry
every time you mess things up!

259
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:39,733
That's always been you!

260
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:43,900
But Edward, all your apologies
won't change our lives.

261
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:49,067
The way your parents look
at you won't change

262
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:51,467
if this is all we're ever
going to be.

263
00:19:01,367 --> 00:19:03,167
Since I clearly
can't rely on you...

264
00:19:05,967 --> 00:19:08,767
I guess I'll just have
to figure out a way again

265
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:11,067
so we're not a burden
in this house.

266
00:19:13,367 --> 00:19:14,067
What do you mean?

267
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:19,767
Thea.

268
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:20,500
Thea!

269
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:22,600
Thea, what are you going to do?

270
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:27,067
You have to do something, Paolo.

271
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:30,800
Find a way to stop Mr. Lorenzo
from pulling out

272
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:34,733
as our major investor
in this project.

273
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:35,467
Don't worry, Dad.

274
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:36,900
I already talked to our VP.

275
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:38,633
He's meeting Mr. Lorenzo
tomorrow

276
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:40,600
to present a revised
partnership deal.

277
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:42,267
No, no, no.

278
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:44,300
That's not good enough.

279
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:47,133
You should handle
this personally.

280
00:19:47,267 --> 00:19:48,267
Okay?

281
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:50,767
This is our biggest
project yet, Paolo.

282
00:19:53,433 --> 00:19:55,600
We're not just a brokerage firm
anymore.

283
00:19:56,933 --> 00:20:00,867
We're a real estate
developer now.

284
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:05,533
We cannot allow this to fail.

285
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:06,733
I know, Dad.

286
00:20:06,867 --> 00:20:08,633
But my daughter is lying
in a hospital bed,

287
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:10,367
fighting for her life.

288
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:13,500
I shouldn't leave her side
just like that...

289
00:20:13,633 --> 00:20:14,400
like I did today.

290
00:20:17,033 --> 00:20:17,633
Why?

291
00:20:18,633 --> 00:20:20,433
Will Jasmine suddenly get
better

292
00:20:20,567 --> 00:20:22,667
just because
you stay beside her?

293
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,000
You have to be realistic, Paolo.

294
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:30,633
If the business collapses,

295
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:34,100
how are you going to pay
for your daughter's treatment?

296
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,867
If you let this company fail,

297
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,033
you're letting Jasmine down,
too.

298
00:20:47,167 --> 00:20:48,067
But Dad, maybe...

299
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:51,500
Let Marj take care of things
at the hospital.

300
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:53,500
She's the woman.

301
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:56,700
The mother.

302
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:58,167
That's where she belongs.

303
00:21:00,333 --> 00:21:02,700
You focus on the company
problem,

304
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:05,600
so you can make sure
Jasmine gets

305
00:21:05,733 --> 00:21:07,700
the best medical treatment
possible.

306
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,133
<i> Love...</i>

307
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:24,433
<i>I'm sorry if I raised my voice
earlier.</i>

308
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:26,967
<i>I tried to delegate
the work, but...</i>

309
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:29,200
Dad wouldn't allow it.

310
00:21:30,967 --> 00:21:32,067
He wants me to take charge.

311
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:35,067
So it looks like I won't
be able to come back

312
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,467
to the hospital for now.

313
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:39,400
Love, she woke up a bit earlier.

314
00:21:39,533 --> 00:21:41,700
The first thing she asked
about was you.

315
00:21:41,867 --> 00:21:44,233
<i>She kept asking what time
you're coming.</i>

316
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:52,967
<i>Tell her I'll call her
in the morning, okay?</i>

317
00:21:54,433 --> 00:21:55,267
<i> But I promise.</i>

318
00:21:56,633 --> 00:21:57,467
I'll go to the hospital

319
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,567
as soon as everything here
is sorted out.

320
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:02,133
Love, when will that be?

321
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:03,433
Just give me some time.

322
00:22:04,667 --> 00:22:07,033
Once I finish all my
responsibilities here,

323
00:22:08,067 --> 00:22:09,400
then I can focus
all my attention

324
00:22:09,533 --> 00:22:11,233
on you and Jasmine, okay?

325
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,100
Sir, they're here.

326
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:21,167
Okay.

327
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:25,200
Marj...

328
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:26,400
<i> I have to go.</i>

329
00:22:26,533 --> 00:22:27,667
<i> The meeting's about to start.</i>

330
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:28,200
<i> All right.</i>

331
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:29,067
<i> I love you.</i>

332
00:22:39,833 --> 00:22:40,600
Marj?

333
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:43,100
Is this a good time to visit?

334
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:50,400
Really, Edward?

335
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:54,100
Your friend is willing to help
with Jasmine's treatment?

336
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:56,167
Yes.

337
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:59,500
He's a sub-specialist in
pediatric hematology here

338
00:22:59,633 --> 00:23:01,267
in the Philippines.

339
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:05,100
He trains consultants
and specialists...

340
00:23:05,233 --> 00:23:07,400
even Dr. Alvarez.

341
00:23:07,533 --> 00:23:11,300
They might've already talked
about Jasmine's complex case.

342
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:14,500
So he'll probably be here soon.

343
00:23:14,633 --> 00:23:16,500
Thank you so much.

344
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:18,800
You've helped us
more than you know.

345
00:23:18,933 --> 00:23:21,567
You have no idea how
much this means to me.

346
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:27,733
If you ever need
someone to lean on...

347
00:23:28,933 --> 00:23:29,833
I'm here, okay?

348
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:31,900
Just give me a call.

349
00:23:34,667 --> 00:23:37,000
Is Thea okay with you
helping me?

350
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,333
Won't she get mad?

351
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:44,467
I mean, things between us
aren't exactly great lately.

352
00:23:46,067 --> 00:23:47,267
But should we really be worrying
about the adult issues

353
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:49,833
right now?

354
00:23:49,967 --> 00:23:51,700
Jasmine's life is on the line.

355
00:23:52,867 --> 00:23:54,633
Let's set all that aside
for now.

356
00:23:58,467 --> 00:24:00,033
Edward, thank you.

357
00:24:30,867 --> 00:24:32,267
- Love.
- Oh?

358
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:35,467
I brought breakfast before
heading to work.

359
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,800
- Heading to work.
- Yes, here.

360
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:40,567
What are you doing?

361
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,067
I'm sanitizing it.

362
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:46,067
Jasmine can't be exposed
to any viruses from outside.

363
00:24:49,467 --> 00:24:50,400
Love, wait, wait.

364
00:24:51,767 --> 00:24:55,067
No, here, stop.

365
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,233
Come on.

366
00:24:56,367 --> 00:24:58,133
Am I really not even allowed
to kiss my own daughter?

367
00:24:58,267 --> 00:24:59,900
Love, even a simple kiss

368
00:25:00,033 --> 00:25:01,467
it could be a health risk.

369
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:04,067
Here, put this on first.

370
00:25:04,233 --> 00:25:05,300
Go on.

371
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:07,300
It's better to be extra careful

372
00:25:07,433 --> 00:25:10,267
so our daughter's condition
doesn't get worse.

373
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,267
- Doctor, how is she?
- Oh?

374
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:26,267
What were the results
of our daughter's tests?

375
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,233
Ma'am, Sir...

376
00:25:28,367 --> 00:25:33,267
based on the blood tests
and the bone marrow aspiration.

377
00:25:34,267 --> 00:25:36,300
We've concluded...

378
00:25:36,467 --> 00:25:41,100
that Jasmine does have
acute myeloid leukemia.

379
00:25:41,867 --> 00:25:42,967
What?

380
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:46,433
No, no, that's not true.

381
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:49,100
Why would our daughter
have leukemia?

382
00:25:49,233 --> 00:25:50,667
That's not true.

383
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:52,633
Doctor, that's not true.

384
00:25:52,767 --> 00:25:55,000
That's not true!

385
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:56,400
Marj, Marj, Marj!

386
00:25:56,533 --> 00:25:57,700
Marj!

387
00:26:03,633 --> 00:26:05,267
He's still not answering
my calls!

388
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,600
Of course, he won't answer you.

389
00:26:06,733 --> 00:26:08,733
His daughter's sick, remember?

390
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:11,867
So what? He has a daughter
with me, too.

391
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,800
And I'm doing this for Ashley.

392
00:26:13,933 --> 00:26:16,267
That's why he can't just
ignore me.

393
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:19,967
I'll make sure he has no choice
but to face me.

394
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:21,367
What are you planning to do?

395
00:26:21,500 --> 00:26:24,333
I'll tell everyone here

396
00:26:24,467 --> 00:26:25,700
that Ashley is your daughter

397
00:26:25,833 --> 00:26:29,033
if you don't give me
what I want.

398
00:26:29,167 --> 00:26:32,400
If we keep lying and she finds
out later,

399
00:26:32,533 --> 00:26:34,733
she'll only get hurt more.

400
00:26:34,867 --> 00:26:36,700
And she'll lose her trust in us.

401
00:26:37,167 --> 00:26:38,200
Do you really want that?

402
00:26:39,433 --> 00:26:42,200
I need to get back into
Torrecampo Realty

403
00:26:42,367 --> 00:26:43,600
so I can prove myself

404
00:26:43,733 --> 00:26:45,533
to Daddy Greg and Mama Regina.

405
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:48,733
Stephen Lorenzo?

406
00:26:48,867 --> 00:26:51,433
I think I know
how I can get back

407
00:26:51,567 --> 00:26:52,767
into Torrecampo Realty.

408
00:26:52,900 --> 00:26:55,800
And this time, Paolo won't be
able to say no to me.

409
00:26:55,933 --> 00:27:00,433
I want Thea reinstated
starting tomorrow.

410
00:27:00,567 --> 00:27:02,300
Is that clear, Paolo?
